parameters: "Screaming Sky"
endcut/B1
You run from the roof, leaving behind the angelic abomination
that used to be the four astronomers.
Over the course of 15 days, the world,\.\. as you know it,\.\. \C[10]ended.\.\.\.
endcut/Scr1
The true death toll can never be known, but 90%
of humanity is wiped out in half a month.
endcut/Scr2
The angelic abomination that the four astronomers became
are responsible for the vast majority of the death toll.
They fly through the sky screaming, leaving death and
chaos in their wake.
endcut/Scr3
Their victims are syphoned into them, leaving piles of
clothing behind.
What remains of humanity is utterly powerless against
them. They rule over the earth unopposed.
endcut/Scr4
There are some who, in their despair, offer themselves
willingly to them.
They hope the angels' victims are not obliterated,
but rather ascended to a higher state of being.
Perhaps they are taken to a better, kinder world.
A paradise.
Although you have obtained some answers from them
before they lost themselves completely, these offer
little comfort. There are many mysteries that
will forever remain unanswered.
One mystery in particular still \c[5]eats at you.
endcut/Sybil1
Many completely vanished on the final night of the disaster.\.\.\.
Your neighbor \C[3]Sybil\C[0] was among them.
endcut/Sybil2
The door to her home was left open.
endcut/Sybil3
An enormous hole marks the outer wall,\.\.
as if something reached down from the sky and plucked her away.
What really became of her?
\FS[40]\C[2]Screaming Sky\|\|\|\|\^
setAchievement("Ending_ScreamingSky");
